By: St Francis de Sales
---
God did not deprive thee of the operation of his love, but thou didst
deprive Him of thy cooperation. God would never have rejected thee, if
thou hadst not rejected his love. O all-good God. thou dost not
forsake unless forsaken, thou never takest away thy gifts until we
take away our hearts.
